From: tawc
Origin: own

Custom Vulkan WSI for the gfxstream-bridge chroot side.

The WSI presents a gfxstream ColorBuffer id over the `tawc_gfxstream`
Wayland protocol. The compositor resolves that id to an
AHardwareBuffer* through the companion gfxstream patch and imports it
through the existing AHB path. Swapchain images do not use dmabuf fds
on the Wayland wire.

This patch wires the surface, swapchain, acquire, and present
entrypoints. `allocate_swapchain_image()` is still the missing piece;
it intentionally returns `VK_ERROR_INITIALIZATION_FAILED` until the
kumquat `RESOURCE_CREATE_BLOB` + `VkImportColorBufferGOOGLE` path is
implemented. See `issues/gfxstream-wsi-swapchain-alloc-blocker.md`.

